CLH_ENABLE.brief: Set to enable Closed Loop hysteresis compensation

CLH_HTM_ENABLE.brief: Set to enable the application of hysteresis thermal model compensation. Note that if CLH_ENABLE is off, then HTM aplication is automatically disabled.

FFD_ENABLE.brief: Set to enable feed forward dynamic module

FFH_ENABLE.brief: Set to enable feed forward hysteresis module

FFP_ENABLE.brief: Set to enable feed forward proportional module

RESERVED_S4H_5.brief: Reserved for Huang Shan - S4H for backward compatibility

TV_ERR.brief: Indicates whether an invalid temperature was detected

Bias Model.description: The bias thermal model changes the bias power based on ambient temperature.

ARC_DENOM.brief: This register is used to set the nominal resistance for the ARC model. DENOM = 4294967296 / RN.

ARC_FEATURES.brief: Enable features in the ARC model

BTM_ADJUSTDEC.brief: Units to decrease bias by per control cycle when P_WIN_EFF not exceeded for BTM_ADJUSTWAIT cycles

BTM_ADJUSTINC.brief: Units to increase bias by per control cycle when P_WIN_EFF exceeded by demand, but P_WIN not exceedeed.

BTM_ADJUSTMAX.brief: Maximum bias units by which power reduction can reduce bias.

BTM_ADJUSTWAIT.brief: NOT IMPLEMENTED YET Number of control loop cycles for which power reduction conditions must be met before power starts to reduce.

BTM_BASE.brief: Parameter BASE of the Bias Temperature Model

BTM_BIAS.brief: Power bias applied on all the wires (power units)

BTM_BIASMAX.brief: The maximum value that BTM_BIAS is permitted to reach to ensure the power window remains open

BTM_GRAD.brief: Parameter GRADIENT of the Bias Temperature Model

BTM_POWER_MAX.brief: max power calulated with given max allowed wire temperature and input temperature

BTM_TEMPINIT.brief: Parameter TEMPERATURE_INIT of the Bias Temperature Model

BTM_TEMPWD.brief: Parameter TEMPERATURE_WINDDOWN of the Bias Temperature Model

BTM_WIN.brief: Parameter PWIN of the Bias Temperature Model

BTM_WINDOW.brief: Power window applied on the forward path (power units)

CENTRE_ADJ.brief: Resistance delta in mOhms by which resistance demands are adjusted due to centering from DLF

CENTRING_MODE.brief: register for selecting centring model: Power Centre, Absolute Resistance Centre, Relative Resistance Centre

CLH_ADJ_A.brief: Hysteresis adjustment value, combination of delta applied across the hysteresis block and the gain shortfall corrected delta accross the inverted PI model, per axis.

CLH_FEATURES.brief: Flags to control 4W Closed Loop hysteresis features

CLH_GAIN_SF_FACTOR_A.brief: Gain shortfall hysteresis scaling factor. Format is Q1.15 fixed point.

CLH_RDELTA_HYST_A.brief: Hysteresis adjusted rdelta demand, per axis.

COUNTER_CTRL.brief: Counter incremented each time the control loop is executed

COUNTER_MAIN.brief: Counter incremented each time the main loop is executed

COUNTER_POS.brief: Counter incremented each time a new position is provided to the library

COUNTER_TEMP.brief: Counter incremented each time a new temperature is provided to the library

CTRL_FEATURES.brief: Bit field used to enable or disable features: Open-loop, DLF, Dynamic Centring, Octagonal SWIN, Wire break detection.

CTRL_GAIN_A.brief: Proportional gain of the control loop

DLF_BACKOFF.brief: How much maximum Resistance demand will be clipped in a Limit finding event

DLF_ERR.brief: Filtered RDELTA_ERROR (mOhms). Whilst this is below DLF_ERRLIM Firmware is considered in control

DLF_ERRLIM.brief: Threshold value of DLF_Err below which the Firmware will be considered in the out of control state.

DLF_HOTZONE.brief: Resistance range in which the Firmware cannot be out of control

DLF_MAXPDR.brief: Maximum resistance delta applied on an axis (mOhms). This is updated every time a limit finding event is found.

DLF_MINPDR.brief: Minimum resistance delta applied on an axis (mOhms). This is updated every time a limit finding event is found.

DLF_TIMEOUT.brief: Threshold number of cycles of being in the out of control state before Limit finding is applied

DLF_VEL.brief: Filtered RDELTA_VELOCITY (mOhms/cycle). Whilst this is above DLF_VELLIM Firmware is considered in control

DLF_VELLIM.brief: Threshold filtered RDelta velocity above which the Firmware will not be considered in the out of control state.

DUTY.brief: Duty currently applied in number of cycles

FFD_FEATURES.brief: Bit field to control feed forward dynamic feature

FFD_KDYN.brief: Feed forward dynamic control gain, in Q6.6

FFD_PDELTA_A.brief: Feed forward dynamic control output demand, per axis.

FFD_PDELTA_W.brief: Feed forward dynamic control output demand, per wire.

FFD_TC.brief: Feed forward dynamic control time constant, in Q0.12

FFH_FEATURES.brief: Bit field to control feed forward hysteresis feature

FFH_RDELTA_HYST_A.brief: Hysteresis adjusted rdelta demand, per axis.

FFH_RDELTA_HYST_W.brief: Hysteresis adjusted rdelta demand, per wire.

FFP_FEATURES.brief: Bit field to control feed forward proportional feature

FFP_KPROP.brief: Feed forward proportional gain, in (signed) Q4.12

FFP_PDELTA_A.brief: Feed forward Pdelta proportional control output, per axis.

FFP_PDELTA_W.brief: Feed forward Pdelta proportional control output, per axis.

HTMEFF.brief: Mixing factor of rdelta demand and rdelta hysteresis in Q0.16

HTMGRAD.brief: Mixing grad to determine a combination of hysteresis compensated and uncompensated rdelta demands

HTMMAX.brief: Maximum wire temperature above which output consists solely of uncompensated rdelta demands

HTMMIN.brief: Minimum wire temperature below which output consists solely of hysteresis compensated rdelta demands

INPUT_CTRL.brief: Bit field that can be used to enable special debug features

INPUT_POS.brief: Position Demand used by the library

LIB_BRANCH.brief: Branch version number of CML library as in <major>.<minor>.<patch>-<branch>.<release>

LIB_MAJOR.brief: Major version number of CML library as in <major>.<minor>.<patch>-<branch>.<release>

LIB_MINOR.brief: Minor version number of CML library as in <major>.<minor>.<patch>-<branch>.<release>

LIB_PATCH.brief: Patch version number of CML library as in <major>.<minor>.<patch>-<branch>.<release>

LIB_RELEASE.brief: Branch version number of CML library as in <major>.<minor>.<patch>-<branch>.<release>

LINEAR_GAIN_ADJ_A.brief: The amount of compensation applied to be fed to posest to correct it

OIS_AF_SCALE.brief: The coefficient of the linear gain for sacling the OIS and rotation axes depending on Z. Q12.20

OIS_AF_SCALING_EN.brief: Enables the AF dependent OIS scaling

PARAMS_UID.brief: Unique identifier for the parameter file.

POS_FEATURES.brief: Enable features in the position estimation model

POS_FILTCOEF.brief: Filter coefficient for position model. 0 is pass-through while 65536 corresponds to the lowest cut-off frequency.

POS_GAIN_CORRECTION.brief: Gain shortfall correction after the pos estimate filter. In Q2.14

RDELTADEMANDOUTPUT.brief: Delta resistance demands - output of DLA block

RMID_CAL.brief: Calibrated centre of resistance used by PosEst

RMID_W.brief: Centre of Resistance as calculated by Centre Calibration algorithm (mOhms)

RSLACK_AVG.brief: Slack resistance metric averaged over all wires

RTM_BASE.brief: Parameter BASE of the Resistance Temperature Model

RTM_CURV.brief: Parameter CURVATURE of the Resistance Temperature Model

RTM_GRAD.brief: Parameter GRADIENT of the Resistance Temperature Model

RTM_RSCEFF.brief: Scaling factor between TARGET0..1 and RDELTA_DEMAND0..1 as calculated by the Resistance Temperature Model (mOhms per Position Demand unit, in Q8.8 fixed-point)

RTM_RSCEFF_INV.brief: Inverse of RTM_RSCEFF, in Q8.8 fixed-point

RTM_TEMPINIT.brief: Reference temperature at which RTM_BASE is the effective RSC (unaffected by gradients)

RTM_TEMPWIRE.brief: Temperature of the wires as calculated by the Resistance Temperature Model (1/10 C)

RTM_THERMALRES.brief: Parameter THERMAL_RESISTANCE of the Resistance Temperature Model

SCM_FFX_MATRIX_VALUES.brief: Sensitivity calibration matrix values for hybrid drive, in Q3.12

SCM_FFX_TRANSFORM_APPLIED.brief: Centered position with transformation matrix applied for hybrid drive

SCM_INVERSE_MATRIX_VALUES.brief: Inversed sensitivity calibration matrix, in Q3.12

SCM_MATRIX_VALUES.brief: Sensitivity calibration matrix values, in Q3.12

SCM_TRANSFORM_APPLIED.brief: Centered position with transformation matrix applied

STM_BASE.brief: Parameter BASE of the Stroke Temperature Model

STM_GRADHIGH.brief: Parameter GRADIENT_HIGH of the Stroke Temperature Model

STM_GRADLOW.brief: Parameter GRADIENT_LOW of the Stroke Temperature Model

STM_SWINEFF.brief: Stroke window as calculated by the Stoke Temperature Model (Position Demand units)

STM_TEMPREF.brief: Parameter reference temperature at which STM_BASE is the effective SWIN (unaffected by gradients)

TEMPEST_ADJ.brief: Temperature offset between the thermometer and the actuator as calculated by the Temperature Estimation Model (1/10 C)

TEMPEST_FILTMEAS.brief: Filtered temperature from the measurement device (1/10 C)

TEMPEST_GRAD.brief: Parameter C1 of the Temperature Estimation Model

TEMPEST_OFFSET.brief: Parameter C0 of the Temperature Estimation Model

TEMPEST_TEMPAMB.brief: Temperature of the actuator as calculated by the Temperature Estimation Model (1/10 C)

TV_COUNTER.brief: Temperature validation counter, indicating the number of consecutive invalid temperatures measured.

TV_ERRLIM.brief: Maximum number of errors allowed before the temperature invalid flag is set.

TV_ERR_FLAG.brief: Temperature validation flag, indicating if an invalid temperature triggered a power down.

WB_BREAK_FLAG.brief: Wire break flags, indicating whether an open/closed circuit was detected triggering a power down.

WB_COUNTER.brief: Wire break detect counter, indicating the number of consecutive open/closed circuits detected.

WB_ERRLIM.brief: Maximum number of errors allowed before the wire break flag is set.

WB_RESMAX.brief: Resistance threshold used in wire break detection. Maximum threshold above which an open circuit is indicated

WB_RESMIN.brief: Resistance threshold used in wire break detection. Maximum threshold above which an short circuit is indicated

POWER_CENTRE.brief: rmid_w is resistance of powered wire

REL_RESISTANCE_CENTRE.brief: rmid_w is resistance of un-powered wire

clh_params.brief: Parameters for the closed loop hysteresis module

clh_readbacks.brief: Readbacks for the closed loop hysteresis module

ffh_params.brief: Parameters for the feedforward hysteresis module

ffh_readbacks_4w.brief: Readbacks for the feedforward hysteresis module

htm_params.brief: Parameters for Closed loop hysteresis thermal model

htm_readbacks.brief: Readbacks for the Closed Loop hysteresis thermal model
